## Hardware Catalog

### Raspberry Pi 5
**Purpose:** Central edge-computing processor for the Smart Car.
**Connected Modules:** USB camera, MPU-6050 IMU, L298N/L293D motor driver (via GPIO PWM).
**Responsibilities:** Runs CNN (TFLite) for lane following, ArUco detection, FSM navigation logic, multi-threaded sensor/control loops.
**Used By:** Smart Car.
**Communication:** GPIO (PWM to motor driver), USB (camera), I2C-type sensor bus (IMU).
**Notes:** Chosen for sufficient power to run CNN inference + CV pipelines + sensor fusion simultaneously without cloud dependency.

### ESP32-CAM
**Purpose:** Combined microcontroller + camera module (OV2640 sensor) for vision-based edge nodes.
**Connected Modules:** Relay module, LED (Charging Station); none additional in Parking use.
**Responsibilities:** MJPEG video streaming; GPIO actuator control (Charging Station only).
**Used By:** Charging Station (`192.168.0.150`), Smart Parking (`192.168.0.200`), Smart Home (optional face-ID camera source).
**Communication:** HTTP (stream on default port, control on port 81).
**Notes:** Same hardware, different roles depending on subsystem config.

### ESP32 (beacon / AP mode)
**Purpose:** Fixed spatial reference anchor broadcasting a known SSID.
**Connected Modules:** None (pure RF beacon).
**Responsibilities:** Continuously broadcast SSID (`tower_1`–`tower_4`) via `WiFi.softAP()`.
**Used By:** Indoor Localization (4 units).
**Communication:** IEEE 802.11 beacon frames (passive, receive-only from mobile node's perspective).
**Notes:** No data processing on-device; purely a static RF anchor.

### ESP8266 (or ESP32, STA mode)
**Purpose:** Mobile Wi-Fi scanning node mounted on the vehicle.
**Connected Modules:** None additional.
**Responsibilities:** Periodic (5s) `WiFi.scanNetworks()`, filter for `tower_*` SSIDs, POST RSSI JSON to server.
**Used By:** Indoor Localization.
**Communication:** HTTP POST to Flask `/train` and `/locate`.
**Notes:** Station mode (not AP); can be either chip family depending on hardware revision.

### Arduino Mega
**Purpose:** Central edge controller for Smart Home physical layer.
**Connected Modules:** DHT11, Flame sensor, Gas sensor, 3× PIR sensors, light relays, fan relay, window servo, buzzer, ST7735 TFT display.
**Responsibilities:** Non-blocking cooperative task scheduling (`millis()`-based); safety-check task (20ms), env read (2.5s), PIR check (1s).
**Used By:** Smart Home.
**Communication:** Serial/HTTP command intake from Python NLP layer.
**Notes:** Chosen for abundant digital I/O and memory for concurrent sensor polling.

### MPU-6050 (IMU)
**Purpose:** Provides 3-axis acceleration + gyroscope data for vehicle self-perception.
**Connected Modules:** N/A (sensor only).
**Responsibilities:** Supplies raw data for yaw-angle integration (bias-corrected) used in precise turning.
**Used By:** Smart Car.
**Communication:** Onboard sensor bus to Raspberry Pi.
**Notes:** Critical for precise maneuvering independent of wheel-slip errors.

### L298N / L293D Motor Driver
**Purpose:** Drives vehicle motors via PWM, supports differential drive.
**Connected Modules:** DC motors, Raspberry Pi GPIO.
**Responsibilities:** Converts PWM signal into motor voltage/direction; trim factors applied per motor to correct drift.
**Used By:** Smart Car.
**Communication:** GPIO PWM from Raspberry Pi.
**Notes:** Enables independent per-wheel speed/direction control.

### Relay Module
**Purpose:** High-voltage circuit breaker isolated from low-voltage control logic.
**Connected Modules:** ESP32-CAM GPIO (Charging Station); Arduino Mega (Smart Home lights/fan).
**Responsibilities:** Opens/closes charging or appliance circuits safely.
**Used By:** Charging Station, Smart Home.
**Communication:** GPIO digital signal.
**Notes:** Charging Station relay is Active-Low (signal "off" = circuit closed/charging).

### DHT11 Sensor
**Purpose:** Temperature and humidity measurement.
**Connected Modules:** Arduino Mega pin 22.
**Responsibilities:** Periodic climate telemetry (every 2.5s) cached in global vars for reuse.
**Used By:** Smart Home.
**Communication:** Digital single-wire protocol to Arduino.
**Notes:** Relatively slow response time; isolated in its own task to avoid blocking.

### Flame Sensor
**Purpose:** Fire hazard detection.
**Connected Modules:** Arduino Mega pin 24 (active-low).
**Responsibilities:** Feeds highest-priority `runSafetyCheck` task (20ms cycle).
**Used By:** Smart Home.
**Communication:** Digital signal to Arduino.
**Notes:** LOW signal = hazard detected; triggers `STATE_EMERGENCY_FIRE`.

### Gas Sensor
**Purpose:** Gas leak detection.
**Connected Modules:** Arduino Mega pin 26.
**Responsibilities:** Feeds `runSafetyCheck`; triggers automatic fan/window activation on leak.
**Used By:** Smart Home.
**Communication:** Digital signal to Arduino.
**Notes:** LOW signal = hazard; triggers `STATE_EMERGENCY_GAS`.

### PIR Motion Sensors (×3)
**Purpose:** Occupancy/presence detection per room zone.
**Connected Modules:** Arduino Mega pins 33 (Room A), 34 (Room B), 35 (Room C).
**Responsibilities:** Feed `runPirCheck` task (1s cycle) for automatic lighting.
**Used By:** Smart Home.
**Communication:** Digital signal to Arduino.
**Notes:** Supports both automatic (motion) and manual (voice) light control.

### ST7735 TFT SPI Display
**Purpose:** Local visual feedback for telemetry, room status, emergency alerts.
**Connected Modules:** Arduino Mega (SPI bus).
**Responsibilities:** Layered rendering — static grid/labels, dynamic telemetry values, full-screen emergency overlay.
**Used By:** Smart Home.
**Communication:** SPI.
**Notes:** Optimized to minimize flicker/SPI traffic via incremental redraw.

