## Communication

- **HTTP:** Dominant protocol across the project — MJPEG video streaming (ESP32-CAM), REST APIs (Chatbot, Web Platform), GET-based actuator control (Charging Station), POST-based calibration/localization (Indoor Localization), command routing (Smart Home NLP → Arduino).
- **REST:** Structured JSON request/response for admin CRUD (Chatbot `/api/admin/*`), Web Platform command execution matrix, Indoor Localization `/train`, `/locate`, `/data`.
- **Wi-Fi (LAN):** Underlying network for all ESP32/ESP8266 devices; Indoor Localization additionally uses raw Wi-Fi beacon frames (not just IP traffic) as its actual sensing medium.
- **MQTT:** Mentioned as an alternative dispatch protocol option in Web Platform's execution dispatch step (alongside serial and HTTP).
- **WebSocket:** Real-time bidirectional updates — Smart Home UI (system state, transcripts, audio), Web Platform (telemetry broadcast to admin dashboard on emergency events).
- **GPIO:** Physical control signal layer — Raspberry Pi → motor driver (PWM), ESP32-CAM → relay/LED, Arduino → all Smart Home actuators/sensors.
- **Serial:** Option for Arduino command dispatch from higher-level control systems (Web Platform execution dispatch).
- **SPI:** ST7735 TFT display bus (Smart Home).

