## Data Flow

1. **Sensing layer:** Edge devices (ESP32-CAM, ESP32 beacons, Arduino sensors, USB camera) capture raw data (video, RSSI, temperature, motion, audio).
2. **Local/edge inference:** Raw data is processed near-source — CNN steering prediction and ArUco detection on Raspberry Pi; YOLO/MediaPipe classification on parking/charging servers; KNN/IDW on the localization Flask server; wake-word/STT/NLP/TTS/face-ID on Smart Home's local compute.
3. **Actuation:** Inference results trigger local physical actuation (motors, relays, lights, fan, window, buzzer, door lock) via GPIO/serial, typically with a stability layer (smoothing, hysteresis, FSM) between raw inference and actuation.
4. **Telemetry aggregation:** All subsystems push status/telemetry (JSON over HTTP/WebSocket) to the central Web Platform.
5. **Central visualization & control:** The Web Platform renders live dashboards and allows administrators to issue validated override commands back down to specific microcontrollers.
6. **Knowledge/Q&A layer:** The Chatbot operates as a parallel, largely independent RAG service, drawing from a curated knowledge base (managed through the Web Platform's admin panel) rather than live subsystem telemetry.

