## 3. Problem Analysis

| # | Problem | Root Cause | Why It Matters |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Ambiguous command execution | The LLM's free-text output is pattern-matched with `in` substring checks against an unbounded string space | Any hallucinated or paraphrased text containing a magic token fires a real-world action; there's no confidence threshold or schema to reject a bad match |
| 2 | Two competing routers per action | `fuzzywuzzy` pre-router (deterministic, phrase-based) and LLM magic-token convention (probabilistic, prompt-based) exist simultaneously in `clone_main.py` | Behavior differs depending on which router "wins," making the system non-deterministic and hard to reason about or test |
| 3 | Prompt bloat / poor scaling | Every device adds another instruction block to one monolithic system prompt | Latency grows, prompt-injection surface grows, and the "1–2 short sentence" conversational persona competes for prompt budget with 12+ command definitions |
| 4 | No knowledge retrieval | `smart_city_prompt` is one hardcoded sentence | Any real question about the Smart City subsystems (parking, indoor localization, charging, the car) cannot be answered accurately; the assistant either refuses or hallucinates |
| 5 | No conversation memory | Every LLM call sends a single-turn message list | Multi-turn interactions ("turn it back on", "what's the temperature there") cannot be resolved; every command must be fully self-contained |
| 6 | Duplicated pipelines | `main.py` and `clone_main.py` each own a full STT→LLM→TTS→hardware stack | Double maintenance burden, double resource cost, and unclear source of truth in future changes |
| 7 | No hardware safety layer | `RPI/rpi_server.py` accepts and forwards any string as a serial command with no schema or auth | A malformed, hallucinated, or malicious value reaches physical hardware with no validation |
| 8 | No structured tool errors | `call_api()` returns ad-hoc dicts (`{"status": "error", "message": ...}`) with inconsistent shape between the two pipelines | Downstream code (e.g. `_handle_sensor_data`) has to defensively guess the schema, and error states aren't distinguishable (offline vs. timeout vs. invalid command) |
| 9 | No observability | Routing/tool decisions only exist as console `print()` statements | Can't measure routing accuracy, can't replay a failure, can't A/B a prompt change |
| 10 | Latency sources | Full LLM round trip (even for a simple "turn on the lights") when the fuzzy router misses; per-call re-reading/re-building of prompts in the non-cached (`clone_main.py`'s own) `Chatbot.get_full_system_prompt()` is fine (assembled from an already-loaded config dict, not re-read from disk) but still string-concatenated on every call rather than cached like `voice_assistant/chatbot.py` does | Every "chat-shaped" turn pays full LLM decode latency even when a much cheaper path (fuzzy match, tool schema match) would do |

