<file path="scripts/README.md">
# Scripts Module

## Purpose
The `/scripts` directory houses testing loops, transcription tools, audio convertors, alignment scripts, and training routines.

---

## Contents

| File Name | Purpose | Execution Role | Dependencies |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `convert_audio.py` | Converts reference MP3 files to matching WAV channels. | Utility. | `pydub`, `core.config_manager` |
| `split.py` | Splitting recording segments using silent boundaries. | Utility. | `pydub`, `nltk`, `core.config_manager` |
| `transcribe_audio.py` | Transcribes master wave files to transcript texts. | Utility. | `faster_whisper`, `core.config_manager` |
| `train.py` | Synthesizes speaker embeddings and aligns chunks. | Model Training. | `speechbrain`, `torchaudio`, `transformers` |
| `finetune_fastspeech2.py` | Custom trainer parameters to fine-tune conformer weights. | Model Training. | `transformers`, `datasets`, `soundfile` |
| `test_transformers.py` | Legacy CLI client running older streaming loops. | Test Runner. | `ollama`, `pyaudio`, `transformers` |
| `test_xtts_stream.py` | Test harness for Coqui XTTS streaming model. | Test Runner. | `TTS` (XTTS), `sounddevice`, `scipy` |

---

## Startup Order
These files do not run as ongoing background services. They are triggered manually by developers during preprocessing, dataset packaging, model evaluation, and diagnostic verification.

---

## Common Tasks

### Run Transcription Pipeline
To transcribe a voice file:
1. Place reference mp3 into `/data/rawan_voice.mp3`.
2. Convert format to wav:
   ```powershell
   python scripts/convert_audio.py
   ```
3. Run transcription:
   ```powershell
   python scripts/transcribe_audio.py
   ```
4. Segment the text and wav files into training datasets:
   ```powershell
   python scripts/split.py
   ```
